- sys/select.h is not available on ancient HP-UX

-
  -n:</path/to/file> for getting nodes from a file
  -n%'node_[1-20,21-30]'
  warning for -n<non-alphanumeric symbol>

- option for specifying a separator for weight: and task on input

- warning message for usage of long options

-
  -w option for resorting tasks according to their weights (weights of
  their subtrees). This is for reducing idle time at the end of
  processing.

non-blocking write(2) for sending task to the slave hosts/CPUs.

SIGINFO for displaying current status of tasks

SIGUSR1 for trying restore connection to dead client hosts
